issue.title: Add shell completion files in future releases
issue.body:
Hi,

would you mind to add the generated completion files to future release artifacts?
This would save us a few steps of running `./git-lfs completion <shell> > output` when packaging for downstream distributions (Gentoo/Linux in this case).

best regards,
Nils

pull_request.title: track: don't modify `.gitattributes` with `--dry-run`
pull_request.body:
In `--dry-run` mode, we're documented to not modify the disk, which means users will not expect us to be modifying `.gitattributes`.  Fix this by setting the `--no-modify-attrs` flag implicitly if `--dry-run` is set.

Fixes #5557
/cc @GTP95 as reporter

issue.title: Dry-run option ignored
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
I tried tracking a file, but by specifying the `-d` option I expected `git lfs` to only tell me the actions it would do to start tracking it, *without actually tracking it*. Looking at its output, seems it started tracking it instead. Maybe the fact that I didn't commit neither add this file to git yet has something to do with it?
**To Reproduce**
Here's what I did and the relative output:
```Bash
$ git lfs track -d --filename participant-login-poc/crates/client/resources/loading.gif 
Tracking "participant-login-poc/crates/client/resources/loading.gif"
$ git lfs track --filename participant-login-poc/crates/client/resources/loading.gif 
"participant-login-poc/crates/client/resources/loading.gif" already supported
```

**System environment**
I'm running an updated version of Arch Linux.
```Bash
$ git config -l
user.name=Giacomo Tommaso Petrucci
user.email=[redacted]
init.defaultbranch=main
filter.lfs.clean=git-lfs clean -- %f
filter.lfs.smudge=git-lfs smudge -- %f
filter.lfs.process=git-lfs filter-process
filter.lfs.required=true
core.repositoryformatversion=0
core.filemode=true
core.bare=false
core.logallrefupdates=true
remote.origin.url=git@github.com:GTP95/thesis.git
remote.origin.fetch=+refs/heads/*:refs/remotes/origin/*
branch.main.remote=origin
branch.main.merge=refs/heads/main
branch.desktop_application.remote=origin
branch.desktop_application.merge=refs/heads/desktop_application
lfs.repositoryformatversion=0
```

**Output of `git lfs env`**
```Bash
$ git lfs env
git-lfs/3.4.0 (GitHub; linux amd64; go 1.21.3)
git version 2.42.0

Endpoint=https://github.com/GTP95/thesis.git/info/lfs (auth=none)
  SSH=git@github.com:GTP95/thesis.git
LocalWorkingDir=/home/giacomo/git/thesis
LocalGitDir=/home/giacomo/git/thesis/.git
LocalGitStorageDir=/home/giacomo/git/thesis/.git
LocalMediaDir=/home/giacomo/git/thesis/.git/lfs/objects
LocalReferenceDirs=
TempDir=/home/giacomo/git/thesis/.git/lfs/tmp
ConcurrentTransfers=8
TusTransfers=false
BasicTransfersOnly=false
SkipDownloadErrors=false
FetchRecentAlways=false
FetchRecentRefsDays=7
FetchRecentCommitsDays=0
FetchRecentRefsIncludeRemotes=true
PruneOffsetDays=3
PruneVerifyRemoteAlways=false
PruneRemoteName=origin
LfsStorageDir=/home/giacomo/git/thesis/.git/lfs
AccessDownload=none
AccessUpload=none
DownloadTransfers=basic,lfs-standalone-file,ssh
UploadTransfers=basic,lfs-standalone-file,ssh
GIT_EXEC_PATH=/usr/lib/git-core
git config filter.lfs.process = "git-lfs filter-process"
git config filter.lfs.smudge = "git-lfs smudge -- %f"
git config filter.lfs.clean = "git-lfs clean -- %f"
```

comment.body:
Hey,

Thanks for the report.  I can confirm this behaviour and that it's a bug.  I'll try to get a patch out for this relatively soon.  It looks like it should in fact be an easy fix.

issue.title: Fix lockable attribute problem
issue.body:
## Problem
lockable attribute in _.gitattributes_ located on sub-directory could not be enabled.

## Steps for reproduce
See [test repo](https://github.com/exceed-alae/git-lfs-test-for-lockable-problem/).

## Details of fix
Add `**/` to internal path pattern in _.gitattributes_ located on sub-directory if path has no slash or only tail slash.

comment.body: Hmmm, I see the problem with your reproduction steps, but I don't think this is the correct solution.  First of all, it fails tests.  Second of all, I think the better way to handle this would be stripping off the `.gitattributes` directory prefix in the filepathfilter code and then matching the pattern against the stripped string.

commits.message:
Add a script to notarize macOS binaries

We'll want to notarize macOS binaries using the new `notarytool` command
rather than `gon` because the latter uses `altool` under the hood, which
will be disabled as of November 1, 2023.  Create a script that runs the
proper command without echoing the arguments so that we don't include the
password in the log, even if it is filtered.

Use new `notarize` script to notarize macOS binaries

We now need a team ID to notarize binaries, so let's pass one in from
the environment and down from the Makefile into new script.  Use the new
script instead of `gon` because the latter uses the old `altool`, which
will no longer work as of November 1, 2023.

Remove mentions of `gon`

We no longer use this tool, so remove mentions and installation of it.

Merge pull request #5554 from bk2204/macos-notarize

Update notarization to use `notarytool`

issue.title: Fix notarization on macOS
issue.body:
As of November 1, 2023, Apple will no longer accept notarized apps using `altool`, which is used by https://github.com/mitchellh/gon, which we're using.  For v3.5.0, we'll need to either make sure that gon is updated (which it may or may not be) or use a different blocking notarization tool.

Note that Apple's notarization tool `altool` isn't blocking, which is why we don't use it, since it can take some time to complete the notarization but we don't want to complete the operation until it succeeds.

pull_request.title: Update notarization to use `notarytool`
pull_request.body:
As of November 1, 2023, Apple will no longer accept notarized apps using altool, which is used by https://github.com/mitchellh/gon, which we've been using.  Port this code to notarytool, which is Apple's preferred command-line tool.

The secrets have been placed in the regular and CI test secret stores already and this has worked successfully on a test build of the release workflow.

Fixes #5394
